class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n < 1) {
            return false;
        }
        double log = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);
        return log % 1 == 0;
    }
}
```

This solution works by calculating the logarithm of `n` with base 3 and checking if the result is an integer. If it is, then `n` is a power of three. If not, then `n` is not a power of three.

The `Math.log` function returns the natural logarithm of `n`, and `Math.log(3)` returns the natural logarithm of 3. Dividing these two values gives us the logarithm of `n` with base 3. If `n` is a power of three, then this logarithm will be an integer.

